[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626844&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626844&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Has anyone written an updating tool for use in updating domain
databases (preferably in C)?  It would probably be menu driven and
be used mainly to allow a user to add a new domain (host).  It would
prompt the user for various common RRs supplying default answers
where appropriate.  There would be as much validation as possible on
the data entered.  There would also probably be methods for updating
an existing entry and deleting an existing entry.  Of course, it would
only be executable by a select group of people.

If someone else has done some of this and is willing to give it to me
I won't have to start from scratch.  Thanks.

Steve Hubert
University of Washington
hubert@cac.washington.edu

